		<instructions>
			Saute onions, celery, carrot, and butter in a large soup pot, until onions are translucent.
Add flour and curry, and cook 5 more minutes. 
Add chicken stock, mix well, and bring to a boil.
Simmer about 1/2 hour.
Add apple, rice, chicken, salt, pepper, and thyme.
Simmer 15-20 minutes, or until rice is done.
When serving add heated cream.
		</instructions>
		<modifications>
			Heating and adding the cream at serving will improve visual apperance, but costs a pan and &quot;plating time&quot;. Adding a few minutes before serving will work just fine, no heating needed.
